  "translations": {
    "en": "He prohibited selling wine, buying wine, and serving wine. He (peace be upon him) said: 'May Allah curse wine, its presser, its planter, its drinker, its server, its seller, its buyer, the one who profits from it, its carrier, and the one it is carried to.' He (peace be upon him) said: 'Whoever drinks it, his prayers will not be accepted for forty days. If he dies with any of it in his stomach, it is a right upon Allah to make him drink the pus of the people of the Fire and the discharge of adulterers. That will be gathered in the pots of Hell, and the people of the Fire will drink it, melting what is in their stomachs and their flesh.'",
